This is one map that definatly have to play! Well from all these screen shots I have tried to show all the different parts of this map compared to the greatriver. This map has many secrets and i'll talk you through them. Screenshot 1: This is at the top part and in the right pillar. To get to it you have to shoot the wall and make the glass come up, then just to the right of where the glass should be under the water level theres a gap go through that and there should be a hole just walk straight to it as theres an invisibe ladder. Screenshot2: This is again at the top part but now its in the left pillar. To get to it you have to go round the back of the top place to where the m429's are and carry on round the back, then walk straight on the left side. it will take you up onto the roof. Find where abouts the top of the left pillar would be a shoot at it, it will then break and you will find this hiden place. To exit; go over to the right side and walk straight and theres a booster which will push you out and back onto surfing. Screenshot 3: Well this is a bomb site, its located in the first surf bit off the T's spawn. To get to it you need to be on the middle bit inbetween the two spawns and then jump onto the ct side but behind the spawn. Walk along till you get the to bit that sticks up and then turn around and walk straight at it as there is another invisible ladder. When your at the top stop and the shoot at the side just facing down a bit and then it will look like this. Screenshot 4: Well this is an extra part at the bottom bit. To get inside of it you need to drop down into it from the part above. Screenshot 5: This is in jail and the part where my crosshair is can be broken and behind that wall are some weapons and a ramp. Screenshot 6: Well this is another teleporter to the jail part(where your not in it though) To get to it go the same way as you did for the bomb site but instead of going up the ladder carry on walking around the side and then shoot the glass in the middle and it should look like this. Screenshot 7: Well this is just showing you where to talk for the Bomb site and the other jail teleporter. Screenshot 8: This is where the hostages are. To get to them fall to the bottom where the water is and face the two teleports which telport you to the spawns. Now do a 180 degrees. Now walk over to the top - right hand corner, duck down and walk into the wall it will teleport you to the hostages. To exit the hostages face the exit sign and press E. Thanks for reading and hope you enjoy this map! P.S. This map is lots of fun.

Official PORT for Counter-Strike: Source.

(The video above is a preview of CS:GO but applies to CS:S as well)

Due to demands from multiple communities, I ported the CS:GO version of surf_greatriver_2015 to CS:S. I did this with an untouched vmf by transitioning the settings within Wall Worm which allows for an identical version between the two, no corruption or misaligned models/brushes. Huge thanks to Shawn Olson for making this possible.

If you want to find the CS:GO version, you can go here instead.



For a full list of all changes, visit the original here.

Some differences between both versions:

  • Replaced novas with m3's
  • Replaced galil-ar's with regular galils
  • Replaced SSG08's with regular scouts
 
Obviously some lighting quality and certain entities couldn't be carried over.

Version naming of the port will be identical to the CS:GO version. If you happen to confuse the files (for instance by installing the CS:S version in CS:GO and vice versa), you'll get an error message which will let you know.

Unlike CS:GO, CS:S allows the packing of all files, no additional files are included in the download.

SURF_GRAPHIA by Target Practice

- This map is a linear medium/hard surf.
- There are two jails composing of:

SHOTGUN BOOST slug fest:

 ... Boost around jail with your shotgun and kill the opposing players in jail. If a player frees you from jail, you will be teleported to the VOLLEYBALL room in which you must win the match to return to spawn.

and 

VOLLEYBALL:

 ... Shoot the volleyball to the opposing players side. If you win 2 points for your team, you will be sent free. The losing team is teleported back to jail.

- Many thanks go to DragonRock, Guardian Studios, and Solidsurf.
- Special thanks go to Ryan S, Takuma, and Akino.
- Thankyou for the critisisms and ideas throughout the making of this map.
- Thankyou to the entire DragonRock Clan and Community, and for all those who played the open surf_graphia_BETA3.

This map was intended for skill surf servers where there is no jail, and this type of design would not affect game play. May not work properly on all servers! ### Checkpoints! For all servers running a checkpoint system, I already added zones with trigger_multiple. They are named as follows:
  • Spawn Area: stage1
  • Checkpoint 1: stage2
  • Checkpoint 2: stage3
  • Checkpoint 3: stage4
  • Checkpoint 4: stage5
  • End of Map: endzone
  • Bonus Start: bonus1
  • Bonus End: bonusend
